form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-445A (Rev. 1/8/92)

full_text: U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET File or A # A10 534 184 LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 10/29/1993 Date You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. 12/01/1993 Date VIGENTE DE LA HOYA SANCHEZ 8:00 AM 445 S MC DONNELL AVE Time LOS ANGELES CA 90022 LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER Place 1201 SOUTH FIGUEROA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 PROPER COURT ROOM ATTIRE IS REQUIRED ROOM NUMBER: HALL MILITARY PERSONNEL PLEASE WEAR UNIFORM You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445A (Rev. 1/8/92) IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
